Detailed Description

Constants.h: entails all the static variables that get used in the whole program. These were implemented because without them, the coding becomes a lot more harder and tedious as the variables are needed back and forth in a bunch of classes. If need be, they can be changed so that they get passed as arguments to functions in various classes; however, doing so would make life more miserable than it already is.
